Hi, Hello, and Welcome

I'm Alex.

I'm not very good at introductions but whilst preparing for jobs I had to make an elevator pitch... so here is a less formal rendition of that

Hi, I'm Alex. I graduated from the University of Western Australia in 2018. I have a degree in Computer Science and a masters in software engineering. For my thesis I delved into the real of Pedestrian Detection and ended up annotating Caltech dataset and realising its an awful dataset.

In my free time I lift weights, drink coffee, code and play too many games.

This site is an attempt to reduce that game time.

So I hope you enjoy the read and have a flick around!
